SPARCcord - Discord Client for Solaris 7 SPARC
===============================================

SPARCcord is a native Motif/CDE Discord client for SPARCstation systems.
It talks to a headless Chrome bridge server that handles the modern
Discord gateway protocol on your behalf.

IMPORTANT: TWO-COMPONENT SETUP
-------------------------------

SPARCcord requires TWO components to work:

  1. discord-bridge  (runs on a modern Docker host — set this up FIRST)
  2. sparccord       (runs on your Solaris 7 SPARC machine — this package)

The bridge handles Discord's HTTPS/WebSocket protocols using headless
Chromium, and exposes a simple HTTP/1.0 API that the SPARC client polls.

STEP 1: Set up discord-bridge (on your Docker host)
----------------------------------------------------

  git clone https://github.com/firefly128/discord-bridge
  cd discord-bridge
  cp .env.example .env
  vi .env                     # Add your Discord token
  docker compose up -d
  docker compose logs -f      # Verify it connects

The bridge listens on port 3002.

STEP 2: Install SPARCcord (on Solaris 7)
-----------------------------------------

  pkgadd -d sparccord-1.0-sparc.pkg

STEP 3: Configure
------------------

Edit ~/.sparccordrc and set the 'server' line to the IP of your Docker
host. If using QEMU SLiRP networking, the default 10.0.2.2 should work.

  server=10.0.2.2
  port=3002

STEP 4: Run
-----------

  DISPLAY=:0 /opt/sparccord/bin/sparccord

Or if /usr/local/bin is in your PATH:

  sparccord

Requirements
------------

  - Solaris 7 SPARC (SunOS 5.7)
  - CDE (SUNWdtbas) for Motif libraries
  - X11 (SUNWxwplt) for display
  - Network connectivity to the Docker host running discord-bridge

Project home: https://github.com/firefly128/sparccord
Bridge:       https://github.com/firefly128/discord-bridge
